Subject: AYS scheduler: fix broken SD2.x fallthrough that left inputs empty

`AYSScheduler::get_sigmas` was clearly meant to warn for SD2.x and then
fall through into the SD1.5 branch — the source even has a literal
`/* fallthrough */` comment between the two cases. But the surrounding
construct is `if / else if`, not a `switch`, so C++ doesn't fall through:
when the SD2 branch fires we just log the warning and exit the chain
with `inputs` still default-constructed (size 0).

Two lines later:

    if ((n + 1) != inputs.size()) {
        results = log_linear_interpolation(inputs, n + 1);
    }

`log_linear_interpolation` then runs `linear_space(0.f, 1.f, 0)` — which
computes `(1.f - 0.f) / (size_t)(0 - 1)`, i.e. `1.f / SIZE_MAX` cast to
float — and feeds an empty `ref_x` / `ref_y` into `linear_interp`,
whose binary-search precondition (`ref_x[j+1]` access) reads past the
end of an empty vector. Crashes the host process on any SD2.x +
AYS_SCHEDULER request before the first sampling step. Repros from
node-stable-diffusion-cpp by setting `schedule: 'ays'` on a SD2.1
context.

Fix: collapse the SD1 and SD2 cases into a single branch that uses the
SD1.5 noise levels and emits the existing warning when the model is
SD2 — i.e. honor the original author's stated intent. SD2.x shares
SD1.5's noise schedule shape (same v-pred-or-eps unet, same training
sigma_max ≈ 14.6) so the SD1.5 levels are the closest available
reference, and the warning still tells the user this is best-effort.

Tracking: <upstream issue/PR url here once filed>

diff --git a/src/denoiser.hpp b/src/denoiser.hpp
--- a/src/denoiser.hpp
+++ b/src/denoiser.hpp
@@ -174,10 +174,11 @@ struct AYSScheduler : SigmaScheduler {
